b - Obtain plot using the z-scores of the resiudals Repeat the Residuals vs Fitted Plot using z-scores of the residuals. Add empirical rule horizontal lines at +2+2 and ???2???2. Use these lines to judge whether or not the residuals are normal or there are outliers. Point out any outliers. Point out any floor or ceiling effects. Do you think the residuals are normal?

a<-gg$residuals
mean(a)

[1] 7.923281e-14
sd(a)
[1] 1098.121
zscore<- (a-mean(a))/sd(a)
b<-plot(zscore, gg$fitted.values, xlab = "Z-Score of Residual", ylab = "Fitted Values") 
abline(h = NULL, v = -2,col="red")
abline(h = NULL, v = 2,col="red")

flr = plot(floor(a), gg$fitted.values, xlab = "Z-Score of Residual", ylab = "Fitted Values", main = "FlOOR")

Ceil = plot(ceiling(a), gg$fitted.values, xlab = "Z-Score of Residual", ylab = "Fitted Values", main = "CEILING")

skewness(gg$residuals,na.rm=TRUE)
[1] 0.05447001

1B Inference: Residuals are normal and outliers are present in the graph. The skewness of the distribution is positive hence the distribution is associated with the floor effect as the values are gathered against the floor.
